  "body": "**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**\r\nI have ~26000 blocks in forkchoice when syncing medalla and it seems to be suspended for >20 minute. This is the profiler screenshot:\r\n<img width=\"979\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2020-10-17 at 15 46 42\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10568965/96332745-fdd69b80-108f-11eb-9749-8659d7f59a99.png\">\r\nIt shows us that we have a performance issue in chain.js `getUnfinalizedBlocksAtSlots`. \r\n\r\nNotice that `forkChoice.getCanonicalBlockSummaryAtSlot` is expensive at this time as we have ~26000 unfinalized blocks. \r\n\r\nOur connected peers are reduced to 0 due to this issue.\r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like**\r\nRight now we loop through slots and do `forkChoice.getCanonicalBlockSummaryAtSlot` while forkchoice should support `getCanonicalBlockSummaryAtSlots` and it does the loop only 1 time.\r\n\r\nAlso since our node is not mature enough, we may need to lower the max `count` when serving `beacon_blocks_by_range` request (currently 1000, need to check with the networking spec to see the minimal).\r\n\r\n",
